The paper proposes a novel learning framework for refining HTN methods, which is a subfield of AI planning. The approach involves task insertion and preference modeling, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.LG (machine learning), cs.RO (optimization), cs.SE (software engineering), and cs.PL (programming languages).
